HEADWORD: Scagliola
<hw>Scagl*io"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It. <ets>scagliuola</ets>, dim. of <ets>scaglia</ets>. See <er>Scaglia</er>.]</ety> <def>An imitation of any veined and ornamental stone, as marble, formed by a substratum of finely ground gypsum mixed with glue, the surface of which, while soft, is variegated with splinters of marble, spar, granite, etc., and subsequently colored and polished.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

